CMC Markets’ Cruddas Named U.K. Conservatives’ Co-Treasurer

-- B y   T h o m a s   P e n n y
-- 
2011-06-06T17:07:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-06/cmc-markets-cruddas-named-u-k-conservatives-co-treasurer-1-.html
Peter Cruddas, the founder of CMC
Markets Plc, was named by U.K. Prime Minister  David Cameron ’s
Conservative Party as co-treasurer.  Cruddas, who gave  400,000 pounds  ($654,000) to the
successful campaign against changes to Britain’s voting system
in a May 5 referendum, will work with the existing treasurer,
 Stanley Fink , chief executive officer of International Standard
Asset Management, the party said in an e-mailed statement today.  Cruddas, who founded CMC Markets in 1989, has given  417,000
pounds  to the Conservatives since November 2009, according to
the Electoral Commission website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Thomas Penny in London at 
 tpenny@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at   jhertling@bloomberg.net . 